# .dockerignore — trims the Docker build context and, above all, keeps runtime state
# and secrets OUT of the built image. The Dockerfile bakes only `app/`, but the whole
# repo is otherwise sent to the daemon, and `app/` can accrue local runtime files
# (e.g. a dev vault at app/data/smartbrain.duckdb) that must never land in an image layer.
# NOTE: bare patterns are root-relative — `web/` excludes the SOURCE tree at the repo root,
# NOT the built SPA at app/smartbrain_3000/web (which the image needs and keeps).

# --- Databases, runtime data & secrets: must NEVER be baked into an image ---
app/data/
data/
**/*.duckdb
**/*.duckdb.wal
**/*.sqlite
**/*.db
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/*.pfx
**/*.crt
certs/
wireguard/
bifrost-config.json
emergency-kit*/
recovery-key*

# --- Build artifacts & caches (regenerated cleanly inside the image) ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.py[cod]
**/*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# --- Not needed to build or run the app image ---
.git/
.github/
.gitignore
.dockerignore
docs/
tools/
signaling/
installer/
compose/
web/
*.md
